article.description: — Tyler Thomas had 26 points in Hofstra’s 83-78 victory over Iona on Friday night.
article.headline: Thomas scores 26 points, Hofstra holds off Iona, 83-78
article.linkText: Thomas scores 26 points, Hofstra holds off Iona, 83-78
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- — Tyler Thomas had 26 points in Hofstra’s 83-78 victory over Iona on Friday night. Thomas shot 9 for 14 (6 for 10 from 3-point range) and 2 of 4 from the free throw line for the Pride (2-0). Darlinstone Dubar scored 22 points and added six rebounds. Jaquan Carlos recorded 12 points and shot 3 for 5 (2 for 4 from 3-point range) and 4 of 5 from the free throw line. Quinn Slazinski led the Gaels (1-1) in scoring, finishing with 20 points, 10 rebounds and four assists. Iona also got 17 points, nine rebounds, two steals and six blocks from Nelly Junior Joseph. In addition, Daniss Jenkins had 13 points. NEXT UP Hofstra next plays Monday against George Washington at home, and Iona will take on Vermont on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
